    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, our offensive core is headlined by **Daulton Varsho** (69.94) and **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (69.82). **Daulton Varsho** benefits from an elite matchup against Woods Richardson, whose 4.87 xERA provides the most favorable run-scoring environment of the day, bolstered by a +10% platoon advantage. **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** remains our most reliable asset; even against a decent arm in Ginn, the combination of his premium order placement and the stolen base potential against a slow-delivery pitcher makes him a set-and-forget anchor. **Geraldo Perdomo** (63.08) and **Tyler Freeman** (69.01) also rate as top-tier plays, with **Tyler Freeman** specifically benefiting from a park factor surge that elevates his upside significantly beyond his base projection.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision today involved the backup catcher slot, where **Yainer Diaz** (47.40) narrowly missed the cut behind **Cal Raleigh** (50.44). While **Yainer Diaz** shows strong underlying metrics, the volatility of facing an elite arm like Bennett (1.80 xERA) forced the optimizer to favor **Cal Raleigh**, whose role at the top of the order offers more consistent run-creation opportunities despite a challenging matchup against Ragans. Elsewhere, we are monitoring **Jung Hoo Lee** (45.43) and **Wenceel Perez** (48.44) closely; while both possess game-changing speed, they are facing tough conditions against McClanahan and Gore, respectively, keeping them firmly in the \"marginal\" start category.\n\nRisk management is paramount today as we navigate several high-end arms. **Luis Arraez** (51.14), **Matt Chapman** (53.36), and **Jung Hoo Lee** are all staring down McClanahan, which suppresses their ceiling; however, their inclusion remains necessary to maximize our volume in the 5x5 categories. We are benching **Masyn Winn** (41.36) today, as his efficiency profile failed to eclipse our starting middle infielders. Keep an eye on **Lawrence Butler** and **Jonathan Aranda**, who remain on the bench as they are not currently confirmed in the starting lineups for their respective clubs. With the scarceness of stolen bases remaining our primary concern, the presence of **Bryson Stott** (60.16) in a favorable spot to exploit the opposing pitcher's slow delivery is a key tactical advantage we are banking on to separate us from the pack.",
